The paper deals with network security and intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach also involves the use of machine learning techniques for classification, which could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for a standard network attack taxonomy, which is related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper proposes a preventive list of actions for network administrators, which could be categorized under systems and information theory (cs.SI).
